<BaseLayout title="Our Review Methodology: How We Compare Property Management Software" description="Learn how PropertyManagePro evaluates and ranks property management software. Our 22-point methodology covers features, pricing, user reviews, and compliance." canonical="https://www.propertymanagepro.com/methodology/" lastUpdated="June 14, 2026">
  <h1>How We Review Property Management Software</h1>
  <p>Transparency is critical to trust. Here's exactly how our team evaluates and ranks every property management platform on this site.</p>

  <h2>Our Evaluation Criteria</h2>
  <p>Each platform is scored across 5 dimensions weighted by relevance:</p>

  <h3>1. Feature Completeness (30%)</h3>
  <p>We test 22 core features covering: violations tracking, ARC requests, online payments, maintenance portals, reserve studies, document management, communication tools, native accounting, mobile app, API access, QuickBooks sync, bank integration, insurance tracking, online voting, calendar management, work orders, vendor management, lease tracking, dynamic pricing, channel management, and guest communication.</p>

  <h3>2. Pricing & Value (25%)</h3>
  <p>We analyze starting price, pricing model (per-unit, per-user, flat, tiered), free trial availability, and free plan options. We calculate effective cost for 3 portfolio sizes: 50 units, 200 units, and 1,000 units.</p>

  <h3>3. User Reviews & Reputation (20%)</h3>
  <p>Aggregated ratings from G2, Capterra, and Software Advice. We weight by recency (last 12 months count double) and number of reviews. Platforms with fewer than 50 reviews are flagged.</p>

  <h3>4. Ease of Use & Onboarding (15%)</h3>
  <p>We evaluate onboarding time, support channels (phone, email, chat, knowledge base), training resources, and implementation complexity for different portfolio sizes.</p>

  <h3>5. Integrations & Ecosystem (10%)</h3>
  <p>Number and quality of third-party integrations, API availability, QuickBooks/accounting compatibility, and open ecosystem vs walled garden.</p>

  <h2>Scoring System</h2>
  <p>Each dimension is scored 1-10. Final score = weighted average. The top-ranked platform receives our "Editor's Choice" badge. We round to one decimal place.</p>

  <h2>Affiliate Disclosure</h2>
  <p>PropertyManagePro participates in affiliate programs including Buildium's Partner Program, HOAware Affiliates, Perfect HOA, LotWize, and others. We may earn commissions when you click through and make a purchase. <strong>Affiliate relationships never influence our rankings or reviews.</strong> If an affiliate program exists, it is disclosed on every page.</p>

  <h2>Review Updates</h2>
  <p>We review and update all comparisons quarterly. Pricing and feature data are verified against each vendor's official website. Last revision dates appear at the top of every review page.</p>

  <h2>Editorial Independence</h2>
  <p>No vendor can pay for placement, positive reviews, or removal from our lists. We do not accept sponsored reviews, "premium" listing positions, or pay-for-play arrangements.</p>

  <h2>Contact Our Editorial Team</h2>
  <p>Questions about our methodology? Found an error or outdated data? Email our editorial team at <a href="mailto:editorial@propertymanagepro.com">editorial@propertymanagepro.com</a>.</p>
